♪

01:16.785 --> 01:18.385
(Fight din) (Cheering)

01:18.386 --> 01:19.986
♪

01:25.127 --> 01:26.727
♪

01:31.766 --> 01:32.065
(Gasping)

01:32.066 --> 01:34.101
I hate your kind.

01:34.502 --> 01:36.837
(Grunting) (Crowd din)

01:36.838 --> 01:40.741
♪

01:40.808 --> 01:43.710
You're vermin
infesting our city.

01:43.711 --> 01:44.210
You make me sick.

01:44.211 --> 01:46.513
(Crowd din)

01:46.514 --> 01:48.114
♪

01:53.219 --> 01:54.819
♪

01:59.893 --> 02:01.493
♪

02:06.498 --> 02:06.798
Take her!

02:06.799 --> 02:08.299
Yeah?

02:08.300 --> 02:08.866
What are the odds?

02:08.868 --> 02:10.501
(Fight din)

02:10.502 --> 02:12.771
On Raies, getting lower every on
Raies, getting lower every second.

02:12.772 --> 02:15.206
♪

02:15.274 --> 02:15.907
No, no, no, the other one.

02:15.908 --> 02:17.876
Sinbad? You're joking.

02:17.877 --> 02:18.309
Look at him.

02:18.310 --> 02:20.443
Crowd: (Chanting) Raies!

02:20.444 --> 02:20.878
Raie Raies!

02:20.879 --> 02:23.814
Raie Raies!
 Put this money on Sinbad.

02:23.815 --> 02:27.250
♪

02:27.318 --> 02:27.651
Come on.

02:27.652 --> 02:29.486
(Crowd din)

02:29.487 --> 02:31.689
Fight.

02:31.690 --> 02:34.391
(Whack)

02:34.392 --> 02:35.992
♪

02:39.229 --> 02:40.730
(Chuckles)

02:40.731 --> 02:42.331
♪

02:48.238 --> 02:48.537
Come on!

02:48.538 --> 02:51.674
Finish him!

02:51.675 --> 02:54.275
(Crashing)

02:54.276 --> 03:02.276
♪

03:02.785 --> 03:03.118
(Grunting)

03:03.119 --> 03:06.788
(Grunting) (Scraping)

03:06.789 --> 03:09.456
♪

03:09.457 --> 03:11.859
(Fight din)

03:11.860 --> 03:13.460
♪

03:18.533 --> 03:20.133
♪

03:25.206 --> 03:26.806
♪

03:31.846 --> 03:33.512
(Crack)

03:33.513 --> 03:35.982
(Music slows)

03:35.983 --> 03:38.184
(Crowd din)

03:38.185 --> 03:39.752
(Booing)

03:39.753 --> 03:47.753
♪

03:48.862 --> 03:51.964
♪

03:51.965 --> 03:53.866
(Coins clinking)

03:53.867 --> 03:55.467
♪

04:01.339 --> 04:02.939
♪

04:08.713 --> 04:08.946
Raies.

04:08.947 --> 04:12.515
(Clinking)

04:12.516 --> 04:12.816
(Thud)

04:12.817 --> 04:15.252
(Crowd din)

04:15.253 --> 04:15.618
(Clinking)

04:15.619 --> 04:17.120
I see a future.

04:17.120 --> 04:21.224
Save it for tourists and travellers.
I'm not interested.

04:21.225 --> 04:28.430
A gateway opened...

04:28.431 --> 04:37.039
Shadows are rising. The old ways are
returning while our city burns.

04:37.040 --> 04:41.510
This... is... terrible.

04:41.511 --> 04:43.945
No.

04:43.946 --> 04:45.780
♪

04:45.781 --> 04:47.949
This is good.

04:47.950 --> 04:51.986
(Dramatic orchestral music)

04:51.987 --> 04:53.587
♪

04:59.461 --> 05:01.061
♪

05:06.901 --> 05:08.501
♪

05:14.342 --> 05:17.210
(Crowd din)

05:17.211 --> 05:18.811
♪

05:23.350 --> 05:24.050
I'm sure they were onto us.

05:24.051 --> 05:26.752
They knew we were trying
to fix the books.

05:26.753 --> 05:28.620
So? I'll just fight
somewhere else next time.

05:28.621 --> 05:30.622
Somewhere else next time.
 No. It's too dangerous.

05:30.623 --> 05:32.223
♪

05:35.661 --> 05:36.127
Left-hand side.
The bag.

05:41.868 --> 05:42.234
What? Me?

05:42.235 --> 05:44.169
Yes.

05:44.170 --> 05:46.804
You, big brother.
It's your turn.

05:46.805 --> 05:51.275
I'll distract him. You go for it.
And don't worry.

05:51.276 --> 05:53.377
Today's going to be a good day.
(Chuckles)

05:53.945 --> 05:55.545
♪

05:58.950 --> 06:03.553
♪

06:03.621 --> 06:05.922
You need to watch out for
yourselves out here.

06:05.923 --> 06:06.555
And why would that be?

06:06.556 --> 06:10.693
Well, the market might seem
like a friendly place but it

06:10.694 --> 06:13.229
attracts the worst
kinds of people.

06:13.230 --> 06:14.330
Really?

06:14.331 --> 06:16.799
Hustlers, beggars,
and pickpockets.

06:16.800 --> 06:18.434
Like this one right here.

06:18.435 --> 06:20.936
(Whistling)

06:20.937 --> 06:23.171
There's no need to
involve the guards.

06:23.172 --> 06:23.538
What?

06:23.539 --> 06:26.441
He was stealing from you.

06:26.442 --> 06:28.977
You know what they do
to thieves around here?

06:28.978 --> 06:29.611
They cut off their hands.

06:29.612 --> 06:32.881
Look at him. He's terrified.

06:32.882 --> 06:34.549
Is this man
causing you trouble?

06:34.550 --> 06:36.784
He was attempting
to steal from me.

06:36.785 --> 06:41.889
But he's been caught, he's been shamed,
and we're willing to let it go.

06:41.890 --> 06:43.457
Father?

06:43.458 --> 06:48.129
If I catch you 'round here again...
(Chain metal rattles)

06:48.130 --> 06:50.697
Be more careful in future.

06:50.698 --> 06:52.532
Thank you. We will.

06:52.533 --> 06:56.436
♪

06:56.503 --> 06:56.970
Father, your case.

06:56.971 --> 06:59.406
Your case!

06:59.407 --> 06:59.739
Hmm?

06:59.740 --> 07:02.608
Oh.

07:02.609 --> 07:04.510
They can't have.

07:04.511 --> 07:07.880
♪

07:07.948 --> 07:08.447
You were wonderful!

07:08.448 --> 07:09.781
So convincing!

07:09.782 --> 07:12.117
I was sure you were
going to start crying.

07:12.118 --> 07:12.517
(Laughter)

07:12.518 --> 07:16.688
Another minute of him pointing and
shouting "thief" at me and I would have.

07:16.689 --> 07:17.222
Oh, so sorry.

07:17.223 --> 07:19.825
It would have been nice if you
had at least have warned me.

07:19.826 --> 07:21.260
(Laughter)

07:21.261 --> 07:21.626
Brother.

07:21.627 --> 07:23.495
Yeah, but where's
the fun in that?

07:23.496 --> 07:25.696
Sinbad, you should make life
easy on yourself, be smart like

07:25.697 --> 07:27.698
me. So, you know,
join the guards.

07:27.699 --> 07:28.199
Oh, yes.

07:28.200 --> 07:28.833
(Talking over each other)

07:28.834 --> 07:32.070
Join the guards and be a slave, tazeem?
No, thank you.

07:32.071 --> 07:34.872
Steady pay, a chance to see some action.
Let's not forget

07:34.873 --> 07:37.175
how our women feel about a
man with a bit of power.

07:37.176 --> 07:39.143
How is that girl
you've been seeing?

07:39.144 --> 07:41.278
Oh, she said those
magical words to me.

07:41.279 --> 07:42.045
"I think of you
like a brother."

07:42.046 --> 07:43.280
Ooh!

07:43.281 --> 07:46.149
And then she asked me about
you, which was sickening.

07:46.150 --> 07:46.850
Try being related to him.

07:46.851 --> 07:48.118
(Laughter)

07:48.119 --> 07:48.685
Peace be with you.

07:48.686 --> 07:50.020
And with you.

07:50.025 --> 07:51.759
Come on!
 Ah! Will you be careful.

07:52.156 --> 07:53.756
♪

07:58.028 --> 07:59.628
♪

08:03.800 --> 08:07.436
I never get tired of this view;
City as far as the eyes can see.

08:07.437 --> 08:09.271
(Banging)

08:09.272 --> 08:11.540
So many people, so
many possibilities.

08:11.541 --> 08:14.842
Did I tell you about my
dream the other night?

08:14.843 --> 08:18.779
Was it one where you just stopped speaking?
For a moment?

08:19.115 --> 08:20.748
(Clang) (Grunt)

08:20.749 --> 08:28.749
♪

08:28.823 --> 08:32.256
What is that?
I have no idea.

08:31.759 --> 08:34.628
♪

08:34.695 --> 08:37.398
Whatever it is,
I don't like it.

08:37.399 --> 08:39.433
You hear such things;
Totems, charms.

08:39.433 --> 08:42.702
(Yelling)

08:42.703 --> 08:43.102
(Screaming)

08:43.104 --> 08:45.371
(Laughter)

08:45.372 --> 08:47.540
Don't! We bring bad
luck to the unaware.

08:47.541 --> 08:49.442
(Rattling)

08:49.443 --> 08:51.744
♪

08:51.745 --> 08:53.913
Not now, it can't.

08:53.914 --> 08:58.518
♪

08:58.585 --> 08:58.918
Never mind.

08:58.919 --> 09:02.387
One day we'll get that big score.
And we'll live in a big

09:02.388 --> 09:10.327
house and we'll never have to
worry about anything again.

09:10.328 --> 09:15.533
Brother... I think yo've taken
one too many blows to the head.

09:15.534 --> 09:18.702
(Laughter)

09:18.703 --> 09:20.971
♪

09:20.972 --> 09:23.840
(Crowd din)

09:25.000 --> 09:31.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

09:42.258 --> 09:42.591
Mother.

09:42.592 --> 09:44.926
I had a great day.

09:44.927 --> 09:47.996
We're going to
eat well tonight.

09:53.603 --> 09:53.868
(Gasps)

09:53.869 --> 09:55.571
Hurt.

09:55.572 --> 09:57.839
Who, me?

09:59.141 --> 09:59.673
No, Amala, no, no.

09:59.674 --> 10:03.611
I'm fine.

10:03.612 --> 10:07.948
I keep telling him he
should go to a doctor.

10:07.949 --> 10:08.316
(Patting)

10:08.317 --> 10:10.851
You didn't take him
with you, did you?

10:10.852 --> 10:13.087
No! No, of course not.

10:13.088 --> 10:13.754
'Cause you promised me.

10:13.755 --> 10:19.759
Yes, I promised you, and jamil is far
too smart to follow me around all day.

10:19.760 --> 10:20.327
Aren't you, jamil?

10:20.328 --> 10:24.264
That's right. I've been at
the marketplace trading.

10:24.265 --> 10:27.300
Really?

10:27.301 --> 10:27.900
What were you trading?

10:27.901 --> 10:31.103
Things.

10:31.104 --> 10:31.604
Expensive things.

10:31.605 --> 10:35.141
(Whispers) Expensive things.

10:35.142 --> 10:37.709
You're both terrible liars.

10:37.710 --> 10:41.447
Well, the main thing is we well, the
main thing is we had a good day.

10:44.484 --> 10:44.816
(Clinking)

10:44.817 --> 10:46.484
You see?

10:46.485 --> 10:46.784
Yeah.

10:46.785 --> 10:48.219
(Chuckling)

10:48.220 --> 10:50.188
(Smooch)

10:54.593 --> 10:54.925
(Clinking)

10:54.926 --> 10:56.461
(Gasping)

10:56.462 --> 10:58.596
(Whacking)

11:00.866 --> 11:04.000
Blood money.

11:04.001 --> 11:05.402
What?

11:05.403 --> 11:07.771
(Clinking)

11:07.772 --> 11:09.373
♪

11:09.641 --> 11:11.608
Amah.

11:11.609 --> 11:12.676
No.

11:12.677 --> 11:15.279
♪

11:15.346 --> 11:19.012
You have brought blood money
into this house.

11:19.082 --> 11:21.884
♪

11:21.951 --> 11:22.451
Amah, I swear, no.

11:22.452 --> 11:25.321
You stupid boy.

11:25.322 --> 11:26.822
♪

11:27.057 --> 11:30.159
What have you done?

11:30.160 --> 11:31.727
(Banging)

11:31.728 --> 11:33.796
(Man unclear)

11:33.797 --> 11:36.598
Go! Run, jamil, run.

11:36.599 --> 11:39.967
♪

11:40.169 --> 11:42.537
(Grunting)

11:42.538 --> 11:45.039
Sinbad, wait.

11:45.040 --> 11:46.640
♪

11:49.912 --> 11:51.512
♪

11:54.816 --> 11:57.751
(Grunting)

11:57.752 --> 11:59.620
(Laughing)

11:59.621 --> 12:04.124
♪

12:04.125 --> 12:06.026
Come on, come on.

12:06.027 --> 12:09.762
♪

12:09.830 --> 12:10.062
Hurry!

12:10.063 --> 12:12.732
Hurry!
(Men yelling)

12:12.733 --> 12:14.367
♪

12:14.368 --> 12:15.935
(Clattering)

12:15.936 --> 12:17.536
♪

12:23.743 --> 12:24.075
Come on!

12:24.076 --> 12:26.278
(Rattling)

12:26.279 --> 12:28.179
Come, brother!

12:28.180 --> 12:29.780
♪

12:34.287 --> 12:34.519
No.

12:34.520 --> 12:36.655
Brother!

12:36.656 --> 12:39.056
(Swords clanging)

12:39.057 --> 12:43.594
♪

12:43.828 --> 12:46.096
Brother!

12:46.097 --> 12:54.097
♪

12:56.473 --> 12:58.573
(Ominous music)

12:58.574 --> 12:59.274
I'm so sorry for your loss.

12:59.275 --> 13:04.178
But we must accept the path set out for us.
Do not let this

13:04.179 --> 13:09.350
destroy you. You're a good man.

13:09.351 --> 13:12.853
Thank you, your highness.

13:24.965 --> 13:29.403
Once there would have been a
way to bring back those who've

13:29.404 --> 13:32.772
passed on, to defeat
death itself.

13:32.773 --> 13:33.240
(Birds chirping)

13:33.241 --> 13:36.909
My son... could live again?

13:36.910 --> 13:41.647
I I wish it were so. But under
the emir's regime, science

13:41.648 --> 13:51.590
is our master. Magic, it grows weak and fades.
And so the dead must stay dead.

13:51.591 --> 13:53.458
Gone forever.

13:53.459 --> 13:56.294
♪

13:56.362 --> 14:00.098
He would have been emir one day
and I would have guided his

14:00.099 --> 14:03.668
hand... helped him rule.

14:03.669 --> 14:06.404
♪

14:06.472 --> 14:06.804
(Rattling)

14:06.805 --> 14:09.973
I used to feel sorry for
those people that we'd see.

14:09.974 --> 14:14.111
Stumbling the streets, one hand
missing, marked forever. And

14:14.112 --> 14:17.581
now we're going to
become one of them.

14:17.582 --> 14:20.484
No. No we're not. We've been
in far worse situations

14:20.485 --> 14:23.954
than this before. It's probably
going to take some bribes and we

14:23.955 --> 14:27.723
might need tazeem to put in a
good word for us but we're going

14:27.724 --> 14:30.793
to get out of this.

14:30.794 --> 14:35.831
Even now, behind bars, you
think that you're right, that

14:35.832 --> 14:36.399
everything will work out.

14:36.400 --> 14:42.370
Yes, brother, because it will.
So smile.

14:42.371 --> 14:43.971
♪

14:47.443 --> 14:50.245
Today is going
to be a good day.

14:50.246 --> 14:52.614
(Light laugh) Yeah.

14:52.615 --> 14:55.417
(Door banging)

14:55.418 --> 14:57.018
♪

15:02.724 --> 15:04.324
♪

15:09.964 --> 15:13.166
You are aware of who I am.

15:13.167 --> 15:15.035
♪

15:15.103 --> 15:15.769
Yes. Um, you're Lord Akbari.

15:15.770 --> 15:20.506
And I believe you know my
son, Raies, personally.

15:20.507 --> 15:23.976
No.

15:23.977 --> 15:26.512
I assure you, you do.

15:26.513 --> 15:29.248
(Footsteps)

15:29.249 --> 15:30.849
♪

15:35.588 --> 15:40.187
Like many his age... my son
liked to prove himself a man.

15:41.493 --> 15:43.427
♪

15:43.629 --> 15:47.365
Drinking and gambling, fighting,
which is where he met you this

15:47.366 --> 15:56.406
morning and where you left him lying
in some sordid back street... Dead.

15:56.407 --> 15:58.007
♪

16:02.881 --> 16:03.346
I didn't realize.

16:03.347 --> 16:07.084
My brother, the emir, has given
me permission to deal with

16:07.085 --> 16:10.019
given me permission to deal with
the situation as I see fit.

16:10.020 --> 16:11.821
♪

16:12.022 --> 16:14.223
As I see fit.

16:14.224 --> 16:15.792
♪

16:15.859 --> 16:20.563
Just hours ago, my son...
Was alive.

16:20.564 --> 16:25.734
And now... ♪

16:25.968 --> 16:27.268
Come here.

16:27.269 --> 16:30.371
♪

16:30.639 --> 16:33.809
What does mercy truly mean?

16:33.810 --> 16:35.077
♪

16:35.144 --> 16:39.314
Is it a sign of strength
or one of weakness?

16:39.315 --> 16:42.983
And then I think of your kind
breeding in the alleys like rats

16:42.984 --> 16:47.554
infesting our city and the question
of mercy falls into nothing.

16:47.555 --> 16:56.229
I accept whatever punishment you have for me.
But please... ♪

16:56.296 --> 17:02.435
My brother has nothing to do with this.
This was me and it was me alone.

17:02.436 --> 17:05.038
Get back.

17:06.306 --> 17:06.705
(Fingers snap)

17:06.707 --> 17:09.876
(Keys jingling)

17:09.877 --> 17:12.644
(Banging)

17:12.645 --> 17:14.713
♪

17:14.981 --> 17:17.049
Brother. Brother!

17:17.050 --> 17:19.885
Just go. Just go, please.

17:19.886 --> 17:23.355
♪

17:23.356 --> 17:25.290
(Door clunking)

17:25.290 --> 17:28.760
♪

17:28.827 --> 17:33.430
Now, if mercy means nothing,
I have to ask myself what

17:33.431 --> 17:36.067
punishment would ever be enough?

17:36.068 --> 17:37.635
♪

17:37.702 --> 17:38.102
(Sword clanging)

17:38.103 --> 17:39.837
(Jamil gasping)

17:39.838 --> 17:41.472
Jamil! Jamil!

17:41.473 --> 17:44.241
Jamil!!!

17:44.242 --> 17:45.909
No!

17:45.910 --> 17:50.046
♪

17:50.047 --> 17:54.017
♪

17:54.085 --> 17:54.350
(Banging)

17:54.351 --> 17:56.686
No! No!

17:56.687 --> 17:58.354
Let me out!

17:58.355 --> 18:03.893
As you took someone from me,
so I take someone from you.

18:03.894 --> 18:09.564
Is it enough? No not even close.

18:11.401 --> 18:15.067
Let me out! Come back here!
Let me out!

18:15.338 --> 18:17.238
♪

18:17.239 --> 18:18.973
Jamil.

18:18.974 --> 18:21.042
♪

18:21.243 --> 18:23.278
Jamil!

18:23.279 --> 18:25.079
Get off me!

18:25.080 --> 18:28.749
♪

18:28.750 --> 18:30.852
No!

18:30.920 --> 18:31.152
(Thud)

18:31.153 --> 18:33.020
(Thud) (Groaning)

18:33.021 --> 18:35.856
♪

19:08.888 --> 19:10.288
♪

18:38.093 --> 18:40.494
(Slow instrumental music)

18:40.495 --> 18:42.095
♪

18:46.035 --> 18:47.635
(Door clunking)

18:55.542 --> 18:57.843
(Keys jingling)

19:01.848 --> 19:03.648
(Thudding)

19:06.352 --> 19:07.952
♪

19:11.557 --> 19:13.157
♪

19:16.729 --> 19:18.962
(Crowd din)

19:18.963 --> 19:20.563
♪

19:25.937 --> 19:27.537
♪

19:32.844 --> 19:38.448
He was a good boy. He would have gone
anywhere, done anything for you.

19:38.449 --> 19:41.717
I'm so sorry, Amah.

19:41.718 --> 19:45.555
It's your fault he's dead.

19:53.196 --> 19:56.465
You'll never learn. And now you'll never learn.
And now your brother is gone.

19:56.466 --> 20:00.001
♪

20:00.236 --> 20:03.505
What am I to do with you?

20:03.506 --> 20:08.008
♪

20:08.009 --> 20:12.180
♪

20:12.448 --> 20:14.715
What am I to do with you?

20:14.716 --> 20:17.818
♪

20:18.053 --> 20:19.820
What am I to do?

20:19.821 --> 20:23.457
It is your fault
that he's dead.

20:23.458 --> 20:27.360
♪

20:27.595 --> 20:34.601
It breaks my heart...
To do this.

20:34.602 --> 20:37.604
But I must.

20:37.605 --> 20:41.039
One day, you will understand.

20:41.040 --> 20:42.774
♪

20:42.976 --> 20:45.677
(Sniffing)

20:45.678 --> 20:50.349
You will be cast out to drift,
unable to set foot on land for

20:50.350 --> 20:56.554
more than one cycle of the sun.

20:56.555 --> 21:00.125
This is my gift to you.

21:00.126 --> 21:03.894
My curse so you can learn.

21:03.895 --> 21:09.900
Until you find atonement...
You will never know peace.

21:09.901 --> 21:12.836
♪

21:12.903 --> 21:13.337
(Flames whooshing)

21:13.338 --> 21:15.739
(Sizzling)

21:15.740 --> 21:16.140
(Screaming)

21:16.141 --> 21:18.975
(Screaming) (Clunking)

21:18.976 --> 21:21.678
♪

21:21.746 --> 21:22.045
(Gasping)

21:22.046 --> 21:24.248
Man: Sinbad.

21:24.249 --> 21:26.582
Sinbad.

21:26.583 --> 21:30.653
♪

21:30.720 --> 21:31.053
(Gasping)

21:31.054 --> 21:32.721
(Gasping)
What have you done?

21:32.722 --> 21:34.857
♪

21:34.924 --> 21:37.260
The guards, they're
on their way.

21:37.261 --> 21:39.328
I can't leave him.

21:39.329 --> 21:43.331
Man: Sinbad, you've got to man: Sinbad,
you've got to get out of the city.

21:43.332 --> 21:47.636
♪

21:47.637 --> 21:49.237
♪

21:54.977 --> 21:56.577
♪

22:01.683 --> 22:03.283
♪

22:08.455 --> 22:10.523
(Birds singing)

22:10.524 --> 22:12.124
♪

22:16.029 --> 22:17.629
♪

22:23.670 --> 22:25.870
I've got to get back
to the Garrison.

22:25.871 --> 22:26.205
Sinbad.

22:26.206 --> 22:30.175
Good luck, old friend.

22:30.176 --> 22:31.810
Peace be with you.

22:31.811 --> 22:33.645
And with you.

22:33.646 --> 22:35.246
♪

22:38.883 --> 22:40.518
(Gasping)

22:42.221 --> 22:43.754
(Birds squawking)

22:43.755 --> 22:46.156
(Bell clanging in background)

22:51.129 --> 22:54.031
(Conversation din)

22:54.032 --> 22:58.635
♪

22:58.636 --> 23:00.837
(Panting)

23:00.838 --> 23:02.438
♪

23:05.743 --> 23:07.343
♪

23:21.258 --> 23:21.757
What have you got?

23:21.758 --> 23:25.994
These furs and leather heading
for the market in (Unclear)

23:25.995 --> 23:28.229
You must be a long way from home, northerner.

23:28.230 --> 23:30.896
It must be a change from the snow and cold.

23:31.700 --> 23:34.201
It'll still be there
when I get back.

23:34.202 --> 23:37.772
(Clucking)

23:37.773 --> 23:40.341
(Light adventure music)

23:40.342 --> 23:43.577
♪

23:44.812 --> 23:49.583
♪

23:49.584 --> 23:52.753
(Clucking)

23:52.754 --> 23:54.354
♪

24:00.260 --> 24:01.494
(Thud)

24:01.495 --> 24:09.495
♪

24:11.505 --> 24:13.105
(Doors bang)

24:13.173 --> 24:13.406
(Slam)

24:13.407 --> 24:19.411
I'm sorry. I must have taken a wrong turn.
I don't know how I ended up here.

24:19.845 --> 24:21.613
(Pained gasp) (Clink)

24:26.018 --> 24:28.186
They are mine.

24:28.187 --> 24:30.421
♪

24:30.422 --> 24:31.522
Hey.

24:31.523 --> 24:33.123
♪

24:37.662 --> 24:38.962
(Clink)

24:38.963 --> 24:43.066
♪

24:43.067 --> 24:44.702
(Shouting)

24:44.703 --> 24:46.502
Gang way. Come on.

24:46.503 --> 24:48.604
♪

24:48.605 --> 24:51.808
(Thumping)

24:51.875 --> 24:52.308
What was that?

24:52.309 --> 24:54.744
I think we've set sail.

24:54.745 --> 24:57.213
No. Not yet.

24:57.548 --> 25:00.015
Not yet.
(Footsteps)

25:00.016 --> 25:01.616
♪

25:05.688 --> 25:08.657
(Boards creaking)
(Frustrated groan)

25:08.658 --> 25:10.258
♪

25:16.332 --> 25:17.932
♪

25:32.051 --> 25:33.885
(Light adventure music)

25:33.886 --> 25:35.419
(Gasp)

25:35.420 --> 25:38.456
(Vomiting) (Spits)

25:38.457 --> 25:41.091
(Groans)

25:43.027 --> 25:47.330
I haven't quite
found my sea legs yet.

25:47.331 --> 25:48.065
It's exciting though, isn't it?

25:48.066 --> 25:53.870
The... (Boards creaking)

25:53.871 --> 25:54.237
(Vomiting)

25:54.238 --> 25:55.672
(Spitting)

25:55.673 --> 25:57.006
Sorry.

26:00.110 --> 26:02.144
You're not too good either?

26:02.145 --> 26:05.314
I guess I haven't
found my sea legs.

26:05.315 --> 26:06.849
(Soft laughter)

26:06.850 --> 26:08.751
(Gasping)

26:08.752 --> 26:12.754
It seems a little more serious...
than that.

26:12.755 --> 26:14.723
(Clunking)

26:14.724 --> 26:15.156
Don't worry.

26:15.157 --> 26:18.226
I know what I'm doing.

26:18.227 --> 26:18.893
Well, at least, I hope I do

26:18.894 --> 26:23.364
well, at least, I hope I do
otherwise we're all in trouble.

26:25.434 --> 26:29.236
Sorry. I'm... anwar
shabani, the ship's doctor.

26:29.237 --> 26:31.905
(Waves lappininin background)

26:31.906 --> 26:34.041
It's my first time at sea, so.

26:34.042 --> 26:35.609
(Gasps)

26:35.610 --> 26:39.913
Ew. That doesn't look good.

26:42.583 --> 26:42.950
(Pained gasp)

26:42.951 --> 26:45.885
Yes, it might sting
a little bit.

26:45.886 --> 26:50.923
Didn't you meant to tell me that
before you put it on, not after?

26:50.924 --> 26:53.126
Yes. That's a good point.

26:53.127 --> 27:01.399
I'm going to get you some water
and something for your fever.

27:01.400 --> 27:01.667
Oh.

27:01.668 --> 27:04.903
Oh.
(Laughs lightly)

27:08.041 --> 27:10.842
(Gasping)

27:10.843 --> 27:12.978
(Waves crashing)

27:16.182 --> 27:19.249
Just to report, sir, there's an
injured passenger in the hold.

27:19.250 --> 27:21.552
Hold's off limits
to all but crew.

27:21.553 --> 27:22.053
Oh, of course.

27:22.054 --> 27:24.254
Which passenger is it?

27:24.255 --> 27:24.889
I didn't think to ask.

27:24.890 --> 27:28.693
All right, let's
get back there.

27:28.694 --> 27:30.695
(Waves lapping)

27:30.696 --> 27:33.496
Anwar: He's injured.

27:33.497 --> 27:35.231
(Sufuffling)

27:35.232 --> 27:36.933
Get up.

27:36.934 --> 27:39.769
(Gasping)

27:39.770 --> 27:44.074
Well, who are you?

27:44.075 --> 27:45.775
Do you have a name?

27:45.776 --> 27:47.110
(Smack)

27:49.212 --> 27:49.511
Sinbad.

27:49.512 --> 27:54.516
Telmeme then, Sinbad, are you
running to or from something?

27:54.517 --> 27:56.785
From.

27:56.786 --> 28:00.222
The usual way.

28:00.223 --> 28:00.956
Let's see what
the fates have to

28:00.957 --> 28:02.991
let's see what the fates have to
say about you.

28:02.992 --> 28:06.227
♪

28:06.228 --> 28:09.864
♪

28:09.865 --> 28:11.565
(Clang)

28:11.566 --> 28:13.166
♪

28:17.639 --> 28:20.541
Somebody is looking
after you after all.

28:20.542 --> 28:23.910
You're on crew until we reach
the first port of call.

28:23.911 --> 28:26.246
Minimum rations,
minimum comforts.

28:26.247 --> 28:31.583
I wouldn't do that if I were you unless
you want a thief as part of your crew.

28:31.584 --> 28:33.285
You're mistaken.

28:33.286 --> 28:33.886
There is no mistake.

28:33.887 --> 28:35.988
No mistake at all.

28:35.989 --> 28:40.926
Young man, what you took from young
man, what you took from us, is it here?

28:42.328 --> 28:45.029
No. Um... I left it basera.

28:45.030 --> 28:47.365
I can tell you where it is I can
tell you where it is if you want.

28:47.900 --> 28:52.103
It's too late. You have no idea what
you have done, what that meant to us.

28:52.104 --> 28:55.006
Father... 
Maybe I was wrong.

28:57.042 --> 29:01.044
Maybe no one's looking out for maybe no
one's looking out for you after all.

29:01.045 --> 29:05.115
♪

29:05.116 --> 29:07.151
Lock him up in the cell.

29:07.152 --> 29:09.186
Like dog.

29:09.187 --> 29:12.222
♪

29:12.223 --> 29:15.893
♪

29:15.894 --> 29:17.794
(Creaking)

29:22.099 --> 29:23.666
(Clang)

29:23.667 --> 29:25.168
(Lock rattling)

29:25.169 --> 29:27.670
Ah, Sinbad.

29:39.381 --> 29:41.049
(Banging)

29:41.050 --> 29:42.417
(Sighs)

29:42.418 --> 29:46.154
(Boards creaking)

29:49.958 --> 29:53.060
(Wind howling)

29:53.061 --> 29:54.995
(Thunder crashing)

29:58.066 --> 30:00.334
(Boards creaking)

30:03.004 --> 30:04.971
(Squealing) (Panicked gasps)

30:10.510 --> 30:12.846
(Clink)

30:15.282 --> 30:18.918
(Wind howling)

30:24.557 --> 30:27.525
(Grunting)

30:27.526 --> 30:30.595
(Thunder crashing)

30:30.596 --> 30:34.199
Hey, tie everything down.

30:36.635 --> 30:39.303
(Rattling)

30:39.304 --> 30:40.704
(Wind whistling)

30:40.705 --> 30:42.606
(Man shouting orders)

30:44.576 --> 30:47.745
(Water whooshing)

30:52.084 --> 30:53.917
Hello.

30:58.022 --> 30:59.822
(Clinking)

31:04.762 --> 31:05.295
I'm trying to help you.

31:05.296 --> 31:08.031
I'm trying to help you.
 I'm sorry.

31:15.571 --> 31:18.107
(Muffled shout)

31:18.108 --> 31:19.541
Come on.

31:23.113 --> 31:23.745
I was trying to help you.

31:23.746 --> 31:26.214
I said I was sorry.

31:26.215 --> 31:26.915
Please don't kill me.

31:26.916 --> 31:29.083
(Panting)

31:29.084 --> 31:32.220
(Dripping)

31:32.221 --> 31:33.821
♪

31:37.126 --> 31:37.458
(Bubbling)

31:37.459 --> 31:39.560
(Roaring)

31:39.561 --> 31:42.495
(Splashing)

31:42.496 --> 31:44.764
(Screeching)

31:44.765 --> 31:48.135
What is that?

31:48.136 --> 31:48.568
(Screeching)

31:48.569 --> 31:50.370
Sinbad: I have no idea.

31:50.371 --> 31:52.105
(Screeching)

31:52.106 --> 31:55.943
♪

31:55.944 --> 31:59.278
(Screeching)

31:59.279 --> 32:02.014
(Splash)

32:05.618 --> 32:07.586
(Gasping)

32:07.587 --> 32:09.488
(Screeching)

32:12.592 --> 32:13.024
Not another step.

32:13.025 --> 32:17.429
(Screeching)

32:17.430 --> 32:19.130
It don't see us.

32:19.131 --> 32:20.832
(Screeching)

32:20.833 --> 32:23.335
It don't see us.

32:23.336 --> 32:25.470
(Splashing)

32:25.471 --> 32:25.870
(Screeching)

32:25.871 --> 32:29.173
(Screeching) (Prolonged scream)

32:35.113 --> 32:38.548
(Screeching)

32:38.549 --> 32:41.018
Stop. Don't move.

32:41.019 --> 32:43.487
I'll get it to follow me.

32:43.488 --> 32:45.254
(Roaring)

32:45.255 --> 32:48.524
(Splashing)

32:48.525 --> 32:49.859
(Screeching)

32:49.860 --> 32:53.729
(Loud splashing)

32:53.730 --> 32:54.163
(Thunderclap)

32:54.164 --> 32:55.564
Storm demons!

32:55.565 --> 32:55.931
(Roaring)

32:55.932 --> 32:58.167
(Roaring) (Splashing)

32:58.168 --> 33:02.737
♪

33:02.805 --> 33:03.105
(Roaring)

33:03.106 --> 33:06.141
(Screaming)

33:06.142 --> 33:06.541
(Shouting)

33:06.542 --> 33:09.611
(Wailing)

33:09.612 --> 33:11.246
(Splashing)

33:11.247 --> 33:13.048
(Shrieking)

33:13.049 --> 33:17.351
♪

33:17.419 --> 33:18.019
Pull! Secure the sail!

33:18.020 --> 33:22.256
Can you hold it?

33:22.257 --> 33:25.559
(Wind gusting)

33:25.560 --> 33:27.395
(Waves crashing)

33:27.396 --> 33:27.995
(Storm demon shrieking)

33:27.996 --> 33:30.364
(Shouting)

33:30.365 --> 33:30.931
Come on, help me!

33:30.932 --> 33:33.433
Come on, help me!
(Waves crashing)

33:33.434 --> 33:36.002
♪

33:36.003 --> 33:39.105
We need to secure the sail!

33:39.106 --> 33:40.706
♪

33:46.813 --> 33:48.413
♪

33:54.421 --> 33:54.653
(Thud)

33:54.654 --> 33:59.289
Man the tiller now!

33:57.924 --> 34:02.428
Man the tiller!
Steer into the wave!

34:02.429 --> 34:03.929
♪

34:03.996 --> 34:08.663
Hurry, Sinbad, hurry! Into the wave!

34:08.367 --> 34:09.967
♪

34:14.906 --> 34:18.476
(Waves crashing)

34:18.476 --> 34:20.077
♪

34:25.049 --> 34:26.949
(Shouting) (Waves crashing)

34:26.951 --> 34:28.551
♪

34:33.757 --> 34:35.092
(Storm demon shrieking)

35:07.156 --> 35:08.256
(Whacking)

35:08.257 --> 35:10.190
(Grunts of pain)

34:44.360 --> 34:44.759
(Waves lapping)

34:44.760 --> 34:48.062
(Seagulls calling)

34:48.063 --> 34:50.197
(Melodic instrumental music)

34:50.197 --> 34:51.797
♪

34:56.672 --> 34:58.272
♪

35:03.811 --> 35:05.312
Gone.

35:05.313 --> 35:13.313
♪

35:14.322 --> 35:22.322
♪

35:23.430 --> 35:31.430
♪

35:32.405 --> 35:40.405
♪

35:41.379 --> 35:45.849
What you've stolen, you
have no idea of its power.

35:45.850 --> 35:46.216
Look.

35:46.217 --> 35:48.686
(Clattering)

35:48.687 --> 35:49.052
(Clinking)

35:49.053 --> 35:56.426
The ship! It's listing to one side!
We're sinking!

35:56.427 --> 35:58.728
(Dramatic instrumental music)

35:58.729 --> 36:01.331
♪

36:01.398 --> 36:03.097
The flooding must be coming from
somewhere down here.

36:04.100 --> 36:04.434
(Thud)

36:04.435 --> 36:05.401
(Splashing)

36:05.402 --> 36:07.203
(Groaning)

36:07.204 --> 36:09.339
I can't believe
this is happening.

36:09.340 --> 36:11.072
The water level down here is
staying the same.

36:10.073 --> 36:13.907
There are no gaps and no leaks.

36:13.343 --> 36:15.444
So then it must be coming
from down below.

36:15.878 --> 36:18.680
(Splashing)

36:18.681 --> 36:20.281
♪

36:25.621 --> 36:29.390
We need to seal this up, stop the
water level from rising in here.

36:29.391 --> 36:30.190
With what?

36:30.191 --> 36:31.992
I know where
they store the tar.

36:31.993 --> 36:32.593
Can you melt it down?

36:32.594 --> 36:34.027
On the deck.

36:34.028 --> 36:36.762
Go then. We haven't got much time.

36:36.763 --> 36:39.568
We need to check the fore-hatch,
see if there's flooding there too.

36:40.569 --> 36:41.736
♪

36:42.303 --> 36:45.137
(Maniacal screaming)
(Screaming)

36:45.138 --> 36:46.773
♪

36:46.841 --> 36:47.507
You're not one of them.

36:47.508 --> 36:51.043
They wouldn't scream
like a little girl.

36:51.044 --> 36:53.246
(Splashing)

36:53.247 --> 36:56.750
♪

36:56.817 --> 37:00.519
Help! Help! Help please here!
My leg, I can't move it!

37:00.520 --> 37:00.920
It's trapped.

37:00.921 --> 37:03.856
Alright. Hold on.
We'll get you out.

37:03.857 --> 37:05.124
Don't leave!

37:05.125 --> 37:07.858
We can't let the water level rise up here.

37:07.363 --> 37:09.996
Not if we're going to survive.

37:09.997 --> 37:12.498
We need to seal it up too.

37:12.499 --> 37:12.899
Help me!

37:12.900 --> 37:16.334
The ship, the
ship is sinking.

37:16.335 --> 37:19.204
I know. She told me.

37:19.205 --> 37:21.239
She has been through
a lot today.

37:21.240 --> 37:21.973
Look. We need to heat this tar.

37:21.974 --> 37:24.876
We're running out of time!

37:24.877 --> 37:27.979
Better get a move on then!

37:27.980 --> 37:30.081
♪

37:30.149 --> 37:30.681
What are you doing?

37:30.682 --> 37:33.450
Go seal the other hatch.

37:33.451 --> 37:34.218
Help me please.

37:34.219 --> 37:36.987
Please don't let me drown.

37:36.988 --> 37:39.957
It'll be fine.
I'll get you out.

37:39.958 --> 37:41.058
(Splashing)

37:41.059 --> 37:45.162
♪

37:45.230 --> 37:45.529
(Tapping)

37:45.530 --> 37:50.566
There's one other survivor,
the ship's cook.

37:50.567 --> 37:52.235
♪

37:52.303 --> 37:52.635
(Coughing)

37:52.636 --> 37:54.938
(Coughing) Help me please!

37:54.939 --> 37:56.539
♪

38:02.112 --> 38:03.712
♪

38:09.185 --> 38:09.584
We're safe!

38:09.585 --> 38:12.454
There are two hatches.

38:12.455 --> 38:12.921
Both need to be sealed.

38:12.922 --> 38:15.057
Where's Sinbad?

38:15.058 --> 38:15.457
(Splashing)

38:15.458 --> 38:19.161
(Panting)

38:19.162 --> 38:20.828
(Splash)

38:20.829 --> 38:28.829
♪

38:29.104 --> 38:37.104
♪

38:37.411 --> 38:45.411
♪

38:45.719 --> 38:53.719
♪

38:53.960 --> 38:59.564
Not your time. Not yet. So,
open your eyes, brother. Don't

38:59.565 --> 39:01.900
give up. Open your eyes.

39:01.901 --> 39:04.303
♪

39:04.304 --> 39:06.271
(Deep inhale)

39:06.272 --> 39:14.272
♪

39:14.846 --> 39:22.846
♪

39:23.322 --> 39:23.721
She's there!

39:23.722 --> 39:26.456
(Splashing)

39:26.457 --> 39:28.058
(Coughing)

39:28.059 --> 39:29.659
♪

39:33.231 --> 39:34.964
(Splashing)

39:34.965 --> 39:38.335
♪

39:38.336 --> 39:40.202
(Panting)

39:46.570 --> 39:48.837
(Dramatic instrumental music)

39:48.838 --> 39:50.438
♪

39:54.811 --> 39:57.213
(Footsteps)

39:57.214 --> 40:00.882
♪

40:00.950 --> 40:04.719
I'm sorry. I
cannot find Sinbad.

40:04.720 --> 40:07.420
Perhaps your powers are not
as strong as you believe.

40:08.857 --> 40:10.557
And perhaps that is for the best.

40:09.558 --> 40:14.929
You took a life from him
as it took one from you.

40:14.930 --> 40:17.563
The blood debt is paid.

40:17.633 --> 40:21.366
My brother, you are wise and
I have always listened to you,

40:22.400 --> 40:27.067
but the life of some street rat
is no equal to that of the boy,

40:27.210 --> 40:33.779
who... the boy who one day
would have ruled this city!

40:33.800 --> 40:36.769
I understand...
 how could you!

40:38.919 --> 40:40.554
True.

40:41.357 --> 40:45.922
True. I have no son, no daughter.

40:45.923 --> 40:51.594
 But I loved Raies as if he was my own.

40:51.431 --> 40:55.030
The blood debt is not satisfied.

40:58.372 --> 41:01.104
Sinbad will pay for what he has done.

41:02.508 --> 41:06.276
But the debt of my boy he will
pay!

41:08.012 --> 41:09.612
♪

41:15.119 --> 41:16.420
(Ship creaking)

41:19.991 --> 41:23.058
Well, you should
both be dead.

41:23.059 --> 41:23.493
Thank you.

41:23.494 --> 41:25.662
No, I mean, after what we've been
through, the storm,

41:25.663 --> 41:28.329
those things. We
should all be dead.

41:28.466 --> 41:29.767
